# DEVELOPMENT RULES

1. DO NOT introduce new libraries unless explicitly required.
2. Always use Supabase for:
   - Database
   - Storage
3. Always use Stripe for payments.
4. Always use Auth.js for authentication.
5. Use shadcn-vue for UI components.
6. Use GSAP for animations.
7. Do not implement search engines.
8. Do not implement external CMS.
9. Use Nuxt server routes for backend logic.
10. Validate paid access before rendering content.
11. Keep business logic in server routes.
12. Use role-based middleware for admin routes.
13. Keep the architecture scalable and modular.
14. Prefer simplicity over over-engineering.
15. All sensitive operations must run server-side.
16. Never expose Stripe secret keys.
17. Use Supabase row-level security if needed.
18. Keep file uploads restricted and validated.
19. Always check purchase table before unlocking content.
20. Follow clean folder structure.
21. Dont use emojis, use oh-vue-icons and animations.

Project philosophy:
Minimal.
Modern.
Secure.
Scalable.
Educational-focused.
Pretty with animations.
